narrative: He is 67, a man in the West who values familiar routines and the people he sees most often. On a typical workday, he heads to his sales or office job, spending the bulk of the day interacting with coworkers and customers, answering calls, and keeping things organized behind the scenes. With a college degree, he tends to see learning as something that extends beyond school, through everyday problem-solving and small improvements. Outside of work, he stays connected through a small circle of friends and relatives, trading messages and visits that break up the week. On weekends, he often keeps things simple, seeing relatives when possible, attending occasional community or religious gatherings, and taking time to rest. Across these routines, he places value on reliability, treating others fairly, and doing his share, whether at work, at home, or in the broader community.
